commit.message:
mt32emu-qt: Minor update in DemoPlayer

Some internals changed to make the MIDI event stream suitable for
MIDI recording and subsequent playback on real devices.
Merge branch 'libmt32emu_2_7'

mt32emu: Fixed initialisation of SHA1 digests in ROMInfo objects (#115)

Fixed initialisation of ROMInfo objects which caused crashes of client
applications when accessing the static ROM data. Currently, only builds
with clang-17.0 are affected which is used in MSYS2 environment.
Updated CMake scripts for compatibility with CMake 3.27+

mt32emu-qt: Reset default properties of Synth details button

It had a maximum height limit (for a reason I am not sure of) which caused
the button looking weird on some platforms. Letting Qt do the layout seems
a better idea since it already looks OK on all tested platforms.

mt32emu-qt: Improved output gain spin boxes in Synth properties (#104)

The spin boxes no longer receive value updates when the user is entering a
number directly. For the new value to take effect, the user has to move
the focus or press the Enter key (which also saves the change in settings).
This new behaviour makes the spin boxes a bit less convenient for
"spinning" (using the arrow keys or the mouse scroll) but obviously less
awkward for direct numerical input.
mt32emu-qt: Layout of Synth properties now again depends on platform

mt32emu-qt: Improved controls for the output gain factors (#104)

Added a couple of spin boxes into the synth properties dialog to allow
for finer control over the synth output gain factors.
mt32emu-qt: Improved look of Synth Properties dialog on macOS
Updated mt32emu-qt FreeBSD port to adapt to a recent breaking change

mt32emu-qt: Fixed occasional crashes when JACK audio device started (#106)

On some platforms, when a relatively small JACK buffer size is configured,
the JACK server manages to invoke the first audio rendering callback early
enough, so that the previous implementation of JACKClient sometimes hasn't
had initialised yet. The new implementation activates the JACK client in
a separate step, when the initialisation is complete.

mt32emu-qt: Fixed UI that may show obsolete state of stopped synth (#107)

After stopping the pinned synth, the SynthStateMonitor occasionally left
displaying the last state change generated immediately before stopping,
e.g. the partial states. This happened due to asynchronous nature of state
updates, so now, we explicitly check the synth state before applying such
updates.
mt32emu-qt: Optimised includes in a few places
Bumped mt32emu-qt version 1.11.1 and updated the docs

commit.message:
Fix CoreAudio element name gating

The current check fails when building on an older SDK that doesn't know about
MAC_OS_VERSION_12_0.
mt32emu_qt: Fixed some markdown links in README.md
Bumped mt32emu_win32drv 1.8.1 and updated other docs
Made mt32emu_smf2wav require mt32emu 2.7 and bumped version 1.9.0
mt32emu-qt: Fixed badly encoded localised device names with portaudio

mt32emu-qt: Enhanced CLI for creating MIDI ports at startup (#95)

The command-line interface now provides command "connect_midi" to create
MIDI ports using the system MIDI driver and two options
"jack_midi_clients" and "jack_sync_clients" to create JACK MIDI ports,
either regular or exclusive, as long as the JACK support is compiled in.

mt32emu-qt: Refactored handling of system MIDI ports

- Moved UI-specific code out of MidiDriver so that management of MIDI port
  can be done programmatically with ease. Also improved MidiDriver API
  for clarity.
- Improved a bit the algorithm of selection of a new port name
  in CoreMidiDriver. Also ensured that names of MIDI endpoints are not
  reused.

Updated DOSBox-mt32-patch for adding property mt32.engage.channel1

This property permits changing the channel assignment at the synth start.
By default, MT-32 compatible devices only react on MIDI messages that come
on MIDI channels 2-10 ignoring messages on MIDI channel 1. However, some
tunes involve MIDI channel 1 yet do not initialise the device accordingly.
In such cases, one might fix this by pressing a magic button combination
on MT-32 front panel. Enabling this property has the same effect: the
device starts recognising messages on MIDI channels 1-8 and 10 instead.
Default is false.
Updated README for mt32emu_qt in a hope to clarify the build steps

mt32emu-qt: Fixed some problems with Floating Display on multi-screen systems (#94)

When the application is restarted, the position of the floating window
should now be restored on the same screen where it was previously. Also,
the window geometry is now adjusted to fit into the screen when the display
it is show on is switched off, and each time the floating window shows up.

mt32emu-qt: Slightly improved handling of stopping synth in SMF player

Previously, should the user stop the synth being playing a SMF or a demo
song, the SMF player proceeded with playing subsequent files nevertheless.
Now the MIDI playback is terminated in case of any failure, so the user
may e.g. reconfigure the synth and re-open, then continue MIDI playback
from the last played item.

mt32emu-qt: Implemented playing demo songs for new-gen MT-32 (#84)

Added submenu "Play Demo Songs" to the "Tools" menu. When a Synth profile
exists that refers to one of the new-gen MT-32 ROMs, the list of demo songs
contained within is shown, yet a few of special items to facilitate
playback control.

mt32emu-qt: Implemented UI for selecting timbres on each part (#70)

Added possibility to view timbre banks and select a desired instrument
on each voice part. The timbres are shown in a popup menu split by their
"sound groups" which is displayed when the user clicks on the instrument
name set on the related part in the Channel Status pane.

Also, bumped the minimum required version of mt32emu 2.7 and the target
version 1.11.0 of the mt32emu-qt app.

mt32emu: Added two new functions for retrieving sound group data (#91)

These provide a way to get names of all the standard timbres and how they
are assigned to the sound groups in the control ROM. Additionally, this
makes it easier to find the names of custom timbres.

Also, bumped target version 2.7.0 to enable detection of availability
of the new functions.
